Is what for us,
buddy?

72
00:02:24,011 --> 00:02:26,263
The camping truck,
the camping truck!

73
00:02:27,348 --> 00:02:29,933
<i>♪ Over you ♪</i>

74
00:02:30,017 --> 00:02:31,935
<i>♪ Darling, over you ♪</i>

75
00:02:33,787 --> 00:02:35,439
Dad?

76
00:02:35,523 --> 00:02:36,940
Hey, kiddos!

77
00:02:38,726 --> 00:02:40,477
Surprise!
Huh?

78
00:02:40,561 --> 00:02:41,711
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa!

79
00:02:41,795 --> 00:02:43,046
COVID! And stranger.

80
00:02:43,130 --> 00:02:45,215
Aw, we've talked on the computer
screen lots of times.

81
00:02:45,299 --> 00:02:46,983
We're old friends.
Where are your masks?!

82
00:02:47,067 --> 00:02:49,719
Where's my grandson?
That's what I want to know.

83
00:02:49,803 --> 00:02:52,722
Oh, don't worry, honey,
we have been totally safe.

84
00:02:52,806 --> 00:02:54,391
Two-week quarantine
from Colorado

85
00:02:54,475 --> 00:02:55,625
while we took in
the scenery.

86
00:02:55,709 --> 00:02:58,361
Dad packed for everything.
We didn't even have to shop.

87
00:02:58,445 --> 00:03:00,797
Haven't spoken face-to-face
with another soul

88
00:03:00,881 --> 00:03:01,798
since we left.

89
00:03:01,882 --> 00:03:03,667
Mm. So romantic.

90
00:03:06,787 --> 00:03:09,039
I guess I'll...
go get Scout?

91
00:03:09,123 --> 00:03:11,041
Okay. Alright, I'll
do you one better.

92
00:03:11,125 --> 00:03:12,742
We thought we could take
all the kids

93
00:03:12,826 --> 00:03:14,144
to check out
Mt. Rainier.

94
00:03:14,228 --> 00:03:16,646
Fun!
Can we go, please?

95
00:03:16,730 --> 00:03:18,048
Uh, I'm sorry.

96
00:03:18,132 --> 00:03:20,717
You're say... you want to take
everyone from here?

97
00:03:20,801 --> 00:03:23,053
Those first few months
with a newborn...

98
00:03:23,137 --> 00:03:25,222
Impossible without help.

99
00:03:25,306 --> 00:03:27,506
Only if it's okay.

100
00:03:29,310 --> 00:03:30,327
Okay.

101
00:03:30,411 --> 00:03:32,329
Yes!
Yay! Come on!

102
00:03:32,413 --> 00:03:34,331
Have I told you two
how much I love you?

103
00:03:34,415 --> 00:03:35,832
Because I definitely
love you.

104
00:03:35,916 --> 00:03:37,667
And we love you, too, hon.

105
00:03:37,751 --> 00:03:39,669
We couldn't have asked for
a better daughter-in-law.

106
00:03:40,754 --> 00:03:42,873
She is the mother
of my grandson,

107
00:03:42,957 --> 00:03:45,175
and even if you haven't
gotten around to proposing,

108
00:03:45,259 --> 00:03:47,978
I am gonna call her
what I want to call her.

109
00:03:48,062 --> 00:03:49,980
I don't get why they're not
married, either.

110
00:03:50,064 --> 00:03:51,648
Okay. Time to
hit the road. Zola.

111
00:03:51,732 --> 00:03:53,150
I'll go get Scout.

112
00:03:53,234 --> 00:03:56,486
I can't wait
to meet my grandson!

113
00:04:02,276 --> 00:04:03,360
That's it?

114
00:04:03,444 --> 00:04:05,061
I can go again if
you want.

115
00:04:05,145 --> 00:04:07,464
You'll get a text in 30 minutes
with the results.

116
00:04:07,548 --> 00:04:09,132
Thank you.
All right.

117
00:04:09,216 --> 00:04:11,234
I've almost used all my kits.
I'm so sorry.

118
00:04:11,318 --> 00:04:13,136
It's just that the... the...
The turnout's so high.

119
00:04:13,220 --> 00:04:15,138
Relax, Schmitt.
We have more in the van.

120
00:04:15,222 --> 00:04:16,640
If we run low,
we can go over

121
00:04:16,724 --> 00:04:18,308
to the drive-through site
at Station 19.

122
00:04:18,392 --> 00:04:19,476
They've got extras.

123
00:04:19,560 --> 00:04:21,478
Oh.
Wow. That's amazing.

124
00:04:21,562 --> 00:04:22,679
How did we get
more kits?

125
00:04:22,763 --> 00:04:25,015
20 hours of virtual meetings
with the Fox Foundation,

126
00:04:25,099 --> 00:04:26,750
convincing them it's the right
thing to do... that's how.

127
00:04:26,834 --> 00:04:29,501
You don't just ask your mom?

128
00:04:32,239 --> 00:04:33,356
Ready for you, sir.

129
00:04:33,440 --> 00:04:35,025
Thank you. Why don't you
go ahead and have a seat?

130
00:04:35,109 --> 00:04:36,159
How you doing?
Good.

131
00:04:36,243 --> 00:04:38,295
One of our cashiers tested
positive at the store.

132
00:04:38,379 --> 00:04:40,530
I feel fine, but, you know,
I figured I should make sure.

133
00:04:40,614 --> 00:04:42,098
Good. Smart.
Okay.

134
00:04:42,182 --> 00:04:44,716
Can you take your mask down
a little bit for me?

135
00:04:46,787 --> 00:04:48,972
All right, one more.

136
00:04:49,056 --> 00:04:50,440
Great. All set.
Yeah.

137
00:04:50,524 --> 00:04:51,608
How many days
till I know?

138
00:04:51,692 --> 00:04:52,642
Uh, well,
it's a rapid test,

139
00:04:52,726 --> 00:04:54,277
so about 30 minutes
for your results.

140
00:04:54,361 --> 00:04:55,879
Oh, wow. I won't be late
for my shift, then.

141
00:04:55,963 --> 00:04:56,880
Thank you so much.

142
00:04:56,964 --> 00:04:58,615
You're very welcome.
Thank you.

143
00:05:02,236 --> 00:05:04,988
I wouldn't be the surgeon I am
without you, Meredith.

144
00:05:05,072 --> 00:05:08,491
You taught me to push myself,
to innovate,

145
00:05:08,575 --> 00:05:11,995
to see what's possible,
and to trust my instinct.

146
00:05:12,079 --> 00:05:16,114
And right now, that's telling me
to change to OB.

147
00:05:17,217 --> 00:05:18,635
Go with God?

148
00:05:18,719 --> 00:05:20,136
Meredith wouldn't say that.

149
00:05:20,220 --> 00:05:22,639
I have literally never known
what Dr. Grey is gonna say.

150
00:05:22,723 --> 00:05:24,307
Ooh! Why don't you be me
and I be her?

151
00:05:24,391 --> 00:05:25,809
Oh, how about
you be you<i> and</i> her

152
00:05:25,893 --> 00:05:27,110
so that I can get back
to the testing tent?

153
00:05:27,194 --> 00:05:28,712
She's my mentor!

154
00:05:28,796 --> 00:05:30,614
I don't want to disappoint her
or Bailey or Dr. Webber.

155
00:05:30,698 --> 00:05:31,681
This is stressful.

156
00:05:31,765 --> 00:05:33,183
Well, so is
pissing off Dr. Avery.

157
00:05:33,267 --> 00:05:34,384
Oh, crap... trauma.

158
00:05:34,468 --> 00:05:36,019
I gotta go.

159
00:05:36,103 --> 00:05:38,021
I had to go first!

160
00:05:38,105 --> 00:05:40,357
<i>Dr. Goldberg
to the ICU. Dr. Goldberg to the ICU.</i>

161
00:05:40,441 --> 00:05:41,691
Arthur Beaton,
14 months...

162
00:05:41,775 --> 00:05:43,026
Hold up, Khan.

163
00:05:43,110 --> 00:05:45,028
Chris, did you want
to wait for Hollie?

164
00:05:45,112 --> 00:05:47,163
Or I can set you up with
a video-chat on a tablet?

165
00:05:47,247 --> 00:05:49,165
No. Thank you.

166
00:05:49,249 --> 00:05:51,968
It's... not a good time.

167
00:05:52,052 --> 00:05:53,637
She has work, so...

168
00:05:53,721 --> 00:05:54,804
go ahead.

169
00:05:54,888 --> 00:05:56,773
Arthur Beaton,
14 months,

170
00:05:56,857 --> 00:05:58,508
diagnosed with
multiple VSDs,

171
00:05:58,592 --> 00:06:00,143
cardiomyopathy,
and heart failure.

172
00:06:00,227 --> 00:06:02,279
He's currently on
day 12 of ECMO,

173
00:06:02,363 --> 00:06:04,614
waiting for a transplant,
status 1A.

174
00:06:04,698 --> 00:06:06,783
We thought this would only be
for a few days.

175
00:06:06,867 --> 00:06:09,786
Do a lot of kids with his
condition stay on it this long?

176
00:06:09,870 --> 00:06:11,588
It's unusual.

177
00:06:11,672 --> 00:06:13,390
It means he's strong.

178
00:06:13,474 --> 00:06:15,492
He's already held his own
through several procedures.

179
00:06:15,576 --> 00:06:17,327
None of which have fixed
the holes in his heart.

180
00:06:18,846 --> 00:06:22,098
We're hoping he can hang on
a little bit longer,

181
00:06:22,182 --> 00:06:24,934
until a donor heart
comes through.

182
00:06:25,018 --> 00:06:27,070
I'll be back to you
in a couple of hours, okay?

183
00:06:32,192 --> 00:06:33,610
Chief.
Welcome back.

184
00:06:33,694 --> 00:06:34,944
Mm.

185
00:06:35,028 --> 00:06:37,047
So, uh, this is the car
that got stuck in a truck?

186
00:06:37,131 --> 00:06:38,548
Yep, ran right up
the loading ramp.

187
00:06:38,632 --> 00:06:40,050
They had to cut open
the side of the van. Mm.

188
00:06:40,134 --> 00:06:42,000
Newlyweds, I heard.

189
00:06:43,137 --> 00:06:44,387
Hell of a honeymoon.

190
00:06:44,471 --> 00:06:45,837
Huh.

191
00:06:46,807 --> 00:06:48,224
Shayne Riley, 45.

192
00:06:48,308 --> 00:06:49,993
Unstable pelvis
and lower abdominal pains

193
00:06:50,077 --> 00:06:52,062
after sustaining crush injuries
in an MVC.

194
00:06:52,146 --> 00:06:54,731
Initially unresponsive,
but now alert and orientated

195
00:06:54,815 --> 00:06:56,232
after saline boluses.

196
00:06:56,316 --> 00:06:57,734
Shayne, you are
in good hands now,

197
00:06:57,818 --> 00:06:58,802
and I'm not
just saying that

198
00:06:58,886 --> 00:07:00,603
because Dr. Bailey here
is my wife.

199
00:07:00,687 --> 00:07:03,406
But you are looking
really good, Chief.

200
00:07:03,490 --> 00:07:05,842
All right, this is
Karissa Skolaski, 42.

201
00:07:05,926 --> 00:07:07,677
Vital signs stable,
A and O times three.

202
00:07:07,761 --> 00:07:10,013
Minor lacerations to the face,
arms, and legs.

203
00:07:10,097 --> 00:07:11,014
Patient complains
of headache.

204
00:07:11,098 --> 00:07:12,615
Let's take her
to trauma one.

205
00:07:12,699 --> 00:07:14,451
Shayne?!
W-Where's my husband?!

206
00:07:14,535 --> 00:07:16,753
He's right over there, ma'am.
He's being taken care of.

207
00:07:16,837 --> 00:07:18,621
Oh, Shayne,
I'm sorry, babe!

208
00:07:18,705 --> 00:07:19,889
I didn't mean it!

209
00:07:19,973 --> 00:07:20,990
Wait,
can he hear me?

210
00:07:21,074 --> 00:07:22,492
Uh, he's heavily
sedated, ma'am.

211
00:07:22,576 --> 00:07:24,961
I can hear her just fine.
I'm just not talking to her.

212
00:07:25,045 --> 00:07:26,745
Ever again.

213
00:07:29,550 --> 00:07:31,267
Improving ground glass
opacities,

214
00:07:31,351 --> 00:07:33,603
no pleural effusion
or pneumothorax,

215
00:07:33,687 --> 00:07:36,373
and no signs of stroke
on head CT.

216
00:07:36,457 --> 00:07:38,323
This is great news.

217
00:07:40,494 --> 00:07:42,245
It's not great news?

218
00:07:42,329 --> 00:07:44,414
Great news doesn't matter

219
00:07:44,498 --> 00:07:47,199
if she's too weak
to stay awake.

